<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="235" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,505,711]" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,281,505,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">
<typeStatus box="[151,210,505,531]" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">Type</typeStatus>
data:
</emphasis>
This species was described from a single male collected in an undetermined locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[1294,1380,505,531]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. Unfortunately, the 
<typeStatus box="[328,376,542,568]" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
specimen was not found during the development of this article. However, in the 
<collectionCode box="[1287,1373,542,568]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34925" name="American Museum of Natural History" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">AMNH</collectionCode>
there is a female identified by Friese as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1924" box="[537,819,577,604]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fusciventris" subSpecies="scutellosa">
<emphasis box="[537,556,578,604]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[571,819,577,603]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">fusciventris scutellosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in Guayaquil, 
<collectingCountry box="[1095,1188,577,603]" name="Ecuador" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
which corresponds to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,287,614,640]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mocsaryi">
<emphasis box="[151,170,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[184,287,614,639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">mocsaryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. If the 
<typeStatus box="[369,417,614,640]" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
specimen and the female identified by Friese are conspecific, then 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1924" box="[1176,1321,613,640]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellosa">
<emphasis box="[1176,1195,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1209,1321,613,639]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="235">scutellosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be a junior synonym of the latter species.
</paragraph>
